<item>
            <title>[PIG-2664] Allow PPNL impls to get more job info during the run</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2664</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Implementations of PigProcessNotificationListener don&apos;t have access to much job-related into until after the job is completed. A few minor edits to PigStatsUtil can change that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Expose the JobClient&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Set an initial JobStats object upon kicking off a job. This makes JobId available to clients once it&apos;s assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
